import java.io.File;
import java.io.IOException;

public class SafeApp {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Get the file path from user input
        String filePath = "path/to/file.txt";

        // Validate the file path
        if (new File(filePath).exists()) {
            try {
                // Read the file contents
                File file = new File(filePath);
                Scanner scanner = new Scanner(file);
                String contents = scanner.useDelimiter("\\s+").next();
                // Print the contents
                System.out.println(contents);
            } catch (IOException e) {
                // Handle the exception
                System.out.println("Error reading file: " + e.getMessage());
            }
        } else {
            // Handle the case where the file does not exist
            System.out.println("File not found: " + filePath);
        }
    }
}
```

This code snippet is safer because it checks if the file exists before attempting to read it. This prevents the code from attempting to read a non-existent file, which could lead to a `FileNotFoundException`. 
